WEBVTT

00:06.267 --> 00:08.921
♪♪

00:08.965 --> 00:10.140
Meredith:
Surgeons like to believe

00:10.184 --> 00:12.099
they're the center
of the universe,

00:12.142 --> 00:13.709
that their
million-dollar hands

00:13.752 --> 00:16.451
are the only thing
that matters.

00:16.494 --> 00:20.455
I don't know how you do
the thing you just did...

00:20.498 --> 00:21.630
[ Chuckles ]

00:21.673 --> 00:25.373
...but it -- mm --
was...spectacular.

00:25.416 --> 00:27.114
Mm-hmm!
[ Chuckles ]

00:27.157 --> 00:29.116
Well, I got to give you
a reason to keep me around.

00:29.159 --> 00:30.247
[ Both laugh ]

00:30.291 --> 00:32.728
Well, maybe tonight,

00:32.771 --> 00:34.730
I might just
return the favor.

00:34.773 --> 00:36.471
♪ Nobody tryna play you Ooh.

00:36.514 --> 00:39.561
♪ Red pill, blue,
what to choose? ♪Maybe sooner than that. Hm?

00:39.604 --> 00:42.085
Richard Webber,
are you still on that?

00:42.129 --> 00:44.087
Come on.
I already told you no.

00:44.131 --> 00:46.046
Well, maybe it's time
to reconsider.

00:46.089 --> 00:48.004
Well, what if something
goes wrong, baby?

00:48.048 --> 00:49.788
Trust me.

00:49.832 --> 00:51.573
♪ Fall in love with me tonight

00:51.616 --> 00:53.096
♪ No need to play it cool,
babe ♪

00:53.140 --> 00:55.968
You only need a scalpel
and the patient to use it on.

00:56.012 --> 00:57.144
No one else.

00:57.187 --> 00:58.101
[ Pounding on door ]

00:58.145 --> 00:59.581
I used to believe it, too.

00:59.624 --> 01:00.364
[ Pounding continues ]

01:00.408 --> 01:01.365
Taryn: Levi!

01:01.409 --> 01:02.671
Um, I'll be
right there.

01:02.714 --> 01:03.933
Check your phone.

01:03.976 --> 01:05.326
But that
was before I had kids.

01:05.369 --> 01:07.676
[ Gasps ]

01:07.719 --> 01:09.765
Oh, my God.
What?

01:09.808 --> 01:12.507
Webber's back as residency
director, officially.

01:12.550 --> 01:13.725
What happened to Grey?

01:13.769 --> 01:15.423
Uh, it says she'll be
splitting her time

01:15.466 --> 01:16.946
between doing surgery
and research.

01:16.989 --> 01:17.903
Taryn: Levi!

01:17.947 --> 01:19.079
[ Pounding continues ]Uh...

01:19.122 --> 01:20.950
Oh, it also says
we were supposed to be

01:20.993 --> 01:23.474
in the skills lab
15 minutes ago!
[ Grunts ]

01:23.518 --> 01:24.562
[ Pounding continues ]

01:24.606 --> 01:25.868
Okay. I'm coming!

01:25.911 --> 01:28.827
♪ Stubborn like a mule, babe

01:28.871 --> 01:30.873
♪ Trying to save your pride [ Scoffs ]

01:30.916 --> 01:32.266
What?♪ You ain't got to hide

01:32.309 --> 01:34.485
♪ I can tell how
I look you in the eyes ♪

01:34.529 --> 01:37.097
Truth is, from the time
your patient first gets sick

01:37.140 --> 01:39.447
to the time they're
lying on your table...

01:39.490 --> 01:41.101
Hey.
Hey.

01:41.144 --> 01:42.754
I thought you were leaving
early this morning.

01:42.798 --> 01:44.887
She started seizing when I was
on my way to the airport,

01:44.930 --> 01:46.932
so I hit her with lorazepam,
phenobarbital

01:46.976 --> 01:48.760
and put her in
an induced coma.

01:48.804 --> 01:52.547
And now I need
a world-class neurosurgeon

01:52.590 --> 01:54.026
to help me figure out

01:54.070 --> 01:56.768
why my landmark transplant
patient is circling the drain.

01:56.812 --> 01:58.379
♪ Come fall all the way

01:58.422 --> 02:02.252
...a team of internists,
specialists, and nurses

02:02.296 --> 02:04.080
have already interacted
with that patient

02:04.124 --> 02:05.473
more than you ever will.

02:05.516 --> 02:07.388
♪ No need to play it cool

02:07.431 --> 02:09.259
I was starting to think
you weren't gonna show up.

02:09.303 --> 02:11.566
[ Sighs ] I almost didn't.
I can't stand the whining.

02:11.609 --> 02:13.263
[ Chuckles ] Well, you don't
have to stay long.

02:13.307 --> 02:14.699
Is that Roy?

02:14.743 --> 02:17.049
When you write these
testimonials,

02:17.093 --> 02:18.486
I want you to lay it
all on the table.

02:18.529 --> 02:21.706
I want to know every
diagnosis, every symptom.

02:21.750 --> 02:23.055
Did you lose 40 pounds?

02:23.099 --> 02:24.622
Are you sweating
through your sheets?

02:24.666 --> 02:25.884
Explosive diarrhea.

02:25.928 --> 02:27.495
[ Laughter ]Do not hold back.

02:27.538 --> 02:29.018
Testimonials?

02:29.061 --> 02:30.454
Roy's headed to Washington
next month to lobby.

02:30.498 --> 02:32.108
Won't shut up about it.

02:32.152 --> 02:34.980
We gotta do to the VA
what Barb Simmons did to me

02:35.024 --> 02:36.939
in the fourth grade when I was
hanging on the monkey bars --

02:36.982 --> 02:38.897
pull their shorts down
and expose them.

02:38.941 --> 02:40.943
[ Laughter ]Bastards.

02:40.986 --> 02:43.119
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:43.163 --> 02:45.295
No, it couldn't be.

02:45.339 --> 02:46.644
[ Coughs ]

02:51.475 --> 02:52.302
Sergeant.

02:52.346 --> 02:54.086
Colonel.

02:54.130 --> 02:56.001
Thought you said you'd never be
caught dead at one of these.

02:56.045 --> 02:59.266
Anyone's dying,
it's you, old man.

02:59.309 --> 03:01.920
[ Laughter ]Yeah.

03:01.964 --> 03:03.052
It's good to see
you, man.

03:03.095 --> 03:05.315
Good to see you.
You look good.

03:05.359 --> 03:07.448
Roy, I want to introduce
you to Major...

03:07.491 --> 03:09.493
Owen Hunt,
Army trauma surgeon.

03:09.537 --> 03:11.452
Welcome.

03:11.495 --> 03:13.584
And what delightful disease have
you been blessed with?

03:13.628 --> 03:15.282
None, fortunately.

03:15.325 --> 03:17.240
Um, I'm here because
I'm hoping we might be able

03:17.284 --> 03:18.415
to work together.

03:18.459 --> 03:20.722
I'm starting a study
to prove the link

03:20.765 --> 03:23.551
between burn pits
and your illnesses

03:23.594 --> 03:24.595
so that the VA
will have to auto--

03:24.639 --> 03:25.814
[ Coughing ]You okay?

03:25.857 --> 03:27.381
-Roy.
-Roy?

03:27.424 --> 03:29.948
Roy, Roy!

03:29.992 --> 03:32.168
Put him on his side.
Call 911!

03:32.212 --> 03:34.518
[ Coughing ]

03:40.524 --> 03:42.134
[ Baby crying ]

03:42.178 --> 03:43.092
Is she okay?

03:43.135 --> 03:44.876
Oh, teething.

03:44.920 --> 03:46.791
Well, in that case,
are youokay?

03:46.835 --> 03:49.054
[ Sighs ] I haven't slept,
all I've eaten is

03:49.098 --> 03:51.056
a handful of cereal --
no, no, no, no, no! --

03:51.100 --> 03:52.101
and I'm late for work.

03:52.144 --> 03:53.407
I'm sorry I asked.

03:53.450 --> 03:54.582
[ Crying continues ]

03:54.625 --> 03:55.974
Jo: Thank you.Okay.

03:56.018 --> 03:58.890
I knew how to be alone,
but now I'm alone with Luna.

03:58.934 --> 04:00.675
I'm responsible
for her life.

04:00.718 --> 04:03.068
I'm so tired,
I could drop dead.[ Horn honks ]

04:03.112 --> 04:04.548
Tough stuff being
a single parent.

04:04.592 --> 04:07.334
You don't happen to have
any teething tips, do you?

04:07.377 --> 04:09.510
At this point, I would
try ritual sacrifice.[ Tires screech ]

04:09.553 --> 04:10.685
Earplugs?
Oh.

04:10.728 --> 04:11.903
[ Horn honks ]Man: Help!

04:11.947 --> 04:13.470
I need some help!Okay.

04:13.514 --> 04:15.472
Oh, I'm sorry, I'm sorry,
I'm sorry.

04:15.516 --> 04:16.995
I don't -- I don't know
what's wrong with her.

04:17.039 --> 04:18.780
She just started screaming
and breathing and --

04:18.823 --> 04:20.434
[ Groaning ]Are you in labor?

04:20.477 --> 04:21.957
I'm not due for
a couple more weeks.

04:22.000 --> 04:22.871
Okay, um...

04:22.914 --> 04:24.220
You're pregnant?

04:24.264 --> 04:25.352
Is it mine?

04:25.395 --> 04:26.483
We've been together
for four weeks.

04:26.527 --> 04:27.615
How would it be yours?

04:27.658 --> 04:28.268
I'm gonna page OB.

04:28.311 --> 04:30.008
Oh, I am OB.

04:30.052 --> 04:31.706
Here. Can you, um,
take her to daycare for me?

04:31.749 --> 04:33.142
Bye, baby.
Gladly.

04:33.185 --> 04:35.884
Okay, um, go inside
and ask for a wheelchair.

04:35.927 --> 04:37.277
[ Groaning lightly ]

04:37.320 --> 04:38.582
-Now, now!
-Yeah, okay.

04:38.626 --> 04:39.888
[ Crying, groaning ]

04:39.931 --> 04:41.629
Hi. Congratulations.
You're doing great.

04:41.672 --> 04:43.457
Okay, deep breaths.

04:43.500 --> 04:45.328
Woman over P.A.:
Nurse Tyler to the OR.
Nurse Tyler to the OR.

04:45.372 --> 04:48.418
Grey! I thought you'd be
settled in Minnesota by now.

04:48.462 --> 04:51.508
[ Chuckles ]
I leave later on this evening.

04:51.552 --> 04:54.119
And I'm only going for
a couple of days a week.Mm.

04:54.163 --> 04:56.078
And I'm still your
chief of general.

04:56.121 --> 04:58.080
And as long as you credit
Grey-Sloan

04:58.123 --> 05:00.648
when you save humanity,
you do you.

05:00.691 --> 05:03.651
What I want to know
is why Webber has paged us here

05:03.694 --> 05:04.956
to the skills lab.

05:05.000 --> 05:06.218
And cleared
my whole schedule.

05:06.262 --> 05:07.785
You too?
Yes.

05:07.829 --> 05:10.222
Well, I don't know who approved
this, but it sure wasn't --

05:10.266 --> 05:11.833
I did.

05:11.876 --> 05:12.790
Meredith: Would you like
to tell us why?

05:12.834 --> 05:14.096
Richard: It's a big day.

05:14.139 --> 05:15.880
Not only is it
my first official day back

05:15.924 --> 05:17.404
as residency director,

05:17.447 --> 05:19.536
I'm debuting a new
teaching method,

05:19.580 --> 05:21.582
and the two of you
are going to help me.Uh --

05:21.625 --> 05:22.713
Come on.

05:22.757 --> 05:24.324
Uh...[ Sighs ]

05:24.933 --> 05:27.849
Alright,
attention, everyone.

05:27.892 --> 05:29.416
Today is gonna be a day

05:29.459 --> 05:32.549
that you will remember
for the rest of your careers.

05:32.593 --> 05:36.901
Each one of you is gonna perform
a lap chole start to finish --

05:36.945 --> 05:39.817
on your own.

05:39.861 --> 05:42.994
Today, you will be attendings.

05:43.038 --> 05:45.040
-What?!
-[ Laughing ] Oh, my God!

05:45.083 --> 05:46.998
Are you kidding?He's serious.

05:47.042 --> 05:49.436
Welcome to
the Webber Method.

05:49.479 --> 05:50.524
[ Chuckles ]

05:50.567 --> 05:51.916
[ Cheers and applause ]

05:51.960 --> 05:53.091
I take it back.

05:53.135 --> 05:54.266
What?

05:54.310 --> 05:55.398
You can't
go to Minnesota.

05:55.442 --> 05:56.878
This man has lost
his damned mind.

05:56.921 --> 05:57.835
-Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
-Yes, God!

06:03.885 --> 06:06.235
Hunt, what's going on?Roy Davis, 60,

06:06.278 --> 06:08.237
experienced syncope after
an episode of hemoptysis.

06:08.280 --> 06:10.500
BP is 160 over 100,
and he's tachycardic.

06:10.544 --> 06:12.154
Gonna need chest films
ASAP.

06:12.197 --> 06:13.677
Roy.

06:13.721 --> 06:15.070
They won't show anything good,
I can promise you that.

06:15.113 --> 06:16.593
Roy, I'm here.

06:16.637 --> 06:18.029
He has the same thing I have --
pulmonary fibrosis --

06:18.073 --> 06:19.683
more advanced.

06:19.727 --> 06:21.468
Listen, I know you'd rather
chew gravel than hang out here,

06:21.511 --> 06:22.382
so don't --
I'm staying.

06:22.425 --> 06:23.339
Trauma 1 is open.

06:23.383 --> 06:24.209
Okay, let's
get him inside!

06:24.253 --> 06:25.385
You stay in the lobby.

06:25.428 --> 06:27.343
I'll update you as soon
as I can, okay?

06:27.387 --> 06:29.214
[ Coughs ]

06:30.172 --> 06:31.956
[ Groans ]Niki, you are 5 centimeters

06:32.000 --> 06:34.045
dilated and having
this baby today.

06:34.089 --> 06:35.133
Congratulations.

06:35.177 --> 06:37.309
But it's too early.
I'm not ready.

06:37.353 --> 06:39.268
And -- And -- And today's
our one-month anniversary.

06:39.311 --> 06:41.183
Wow! It's a special day
all around.

06:41.226 --> 06:41.966
Who's the dad?

06:42.010 --> 06:43.272
No dad. Just a hook-up.

06:43.315 --> 06:45.317
We had sex.
A lot of sex.

06:45.361 --> 06:46.841
I had a lot of sex with
a pregnant woman.

06:46.884 --> 06:48.277
It works just the same.

06:48.320 --> 06:49.844
Okay, but, like,
I'm pretty sure that's

06:49.887 --> 06:51.193
outside of
my moral code.

06:51.236 --> 06:52.629
W-Why didn't you tell me?

06:52.673 --> 06:53.761
Look at me.
I thought you knew.

06:53.804 --> 06:54.762
I just
thought you were --

06:54.805 --> 06:56.111
Aaaah!Okay. Uh, Dustin, right?

06:56.154 --> 06:57.678
Uh, Niki is in good hands.

06:57.721 --> 07:00.681
Why don't you take a breather,
go find some ice chips?

07:00.724 --> 07:02.987
For her, not you.

07:03.031 --> 07:04.336
[ Groans ]

07:04.380 --> 07:05.512
Niki, are you okay?

07:05.555 --> 07:06.991
My chest really hurts.

07:07.035 --> 07:08.993
Okay, Wilson, let's get
an EKG and vitals.

07:09.037 --> 07:10.255
Right.

07:10.299 --> 07:11.648
Okay.
Breathe.

07:11.692 --> 07:13.694
[ Breathes deeply ]Good.

07:13.737 --> 07:16.348
Okay, now, this system of
concurrent surgeries will allow

07:16.392 --> 07:19.656
us to put experienced residents
in the OR as leads,

07:19.700 --> 07:21.397
and then attendings
can rotate in and out

07:21.441 --> 07:23.007
for maximum efficiency.

07:23.051 --> 07:24.574
I don't like it.

07:24.618 --> 07:25.967
Look, look.
If you look here,

07:26.010 --> 07:28.448
the average lap chole
lasts what -- 45 minutes?

07:28.491 --> 07:30.188
But the most critical
part only lasts...

07:30.232 --> 07:32.234
5 to 10.
Exactly.

07:32.277 --> 07:34.192
Which means, if each
attending rotates

07:34.236 --> 07:35.411
according to the schedule,

07:35.455 --> 07:37.239
we can be in
each and every OR --

07:37.282 --> 07:39.415
At precisely the moment
we need to be.

07:39.459 --> 07:40.677
Yes.

07:40.721 --> 07:41.809
I still don't like it.

07:41.852 --> 07:43.941
[ Chuckling ]
Bailey, this is the answer

07:43.985 --> 07:45.726
to our biggest challenge
right now --

07:45.769 --> 07:47.249
the physician shortage.

07:47.292 --> 07:48.859
A-And it's lap choles.

07:48.903 --> 07:50.948
It's not transplants
and Whipples.

07:50.992 --> 07:52.994
Look, this generation
of residents --

07:53.037 --> 07:55.823
they don't have a thousand hours
to watch us operate

07:55.866 --> 07:57.389
while we work them
to the bone.

07:57.433 --> 07:59.566
I mean, they want to
work smarter, not harder.

07:59.609 --> 08:00.654
And who would blame them?

08:00.697 --> 08:02.960
I don't need
generation education.

08:03.004 --> 08:05.049
I need patients
not to die.

08:05.093 --> 08:07.138
I've been saying
for a long time that

08:07.182 --> 08:09.271
we need to get the residents
out of the lab and into the OR.

08:09.314 --> 08:10.707
Uh...

08:10.751 --> 08:11.839
What do you say, Bailey?

08:11.882 --> 08:14.232
You ready to do
12 lap choles today?

08:15.364 --> 08:17.888
Look, the system only works
with three attendings.

08:17.932 --> 08:19.847
We all have to be
on board.

08:21.849 --> 08:23.677
God help us. Fine.
Let's do it.

08:23.720 --> 08:25.548
You won't regret it.
Okay.

08:25.592 --> 08:26.549
Let's not go that far.

08:26.593 --> 08:28.290
[ Laughs ]

08:28.333 --> 08:30.161
Woman over P.A.:
Dr. Wagner to radiology.

08:30.205 --> 08:31.989
Dr. Wagner to radiology.

08:33.556 --> 08:35.645
Oh, Hayes, hey.

08:35.689 --> 08:37.995
Do you have a quick second
for a pediatric consult?

08:38.039 --> 08:39.910
For Grey's award-winning
abdomen? Sure.

08:39.954 --> 08:41.999
[ Chuckles ]
A 14-year-old kid,

08:42.043 --> 08:44.088
plays soccer in a park
near our hotel.

08:44.132 --> 08:45.481
Mm-hmm.Seemed to be getting

08:45.525 --> 08:46.874
extra winded
the other day.

08:46.917 --> 08:48.658
Um, his ankles look
a little swollen.

08:48.702 --> 08:50.312
Is that --
Is that anything?

08:50.355 --> 08:52.793
[ Sighs ]
Could be. Or not.

08:52.836 --> 08:54.403
I'm sorry.
I'd have to examine him myself

08:54.446 --> 08:55.883
to tell you anything
more definitive.

08:55.926 --> 08:58.363
I was afraid
you'd say that.

08:58.407 --> 09:00.235
[ Telephone rings in distance ]

09:00.278 --> 09:01.715
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

09:01.758 --> 09:03.412
Roy: So, how'd you meet Noah?

09:03.455 --> 09:05.283
He avoids doctors like
the plague.

09:05.327 --> 09:07.024
I, uh, treated him
and his son recently.

09:07.068 --> 09:09.244
Ah, the accident.
[ Coughs]

09:09.287 --> 09:11.072
That tree will never
be the same.

09:11.115 --> 09:12.900
Or the car.

09:12.943 --> 09:16.251
Noah's the closest thing
I have to a son.

09:16.294 --> 09:19.471
[ Coughs ] Met him when he was
a pimple-faced recruit

09:19.515 --> 09:21.256
whose voice had barely dropped.

09:21.299 --> 09:24.172
I watched him
grow up, get married,

09:24.215 --> 09:26.087
[coughs] have Danny.

09:26.130 --> 09:28.045
Have you met Heather yet?
[ Coughs ]

09:28.089 --> 09:29.873
His wife? No, not yet.

09:29.917 --> 09:33.224
I love Noah, but he punched
above his weight on that one.

09:33.268 --> 09:34.835
[ Laughter ]

09:34.878 --> 09:36.967
The scans are up.[ Beeping ]

09:37.011 --> 09:39.404
Oh, man. Damn it.

09:39.448 --> 09:40.492
See that nodule there?

09:40.536 --> 09:42.233
Lung cancer.

09:42.277 --> 09:43.583
Probably an early stage,

09:43.626 --> 09:45.585
but since he's also got
pulmonary fibrosis...

09:45.628 --> 09:48.370
Might as well be terminal.

09:48.413 --> 09:50.415
All because the U.S. military
couldn't be bothered

09:50.459 --> 09:52.809
to properly dispose
of its trash.

09:52.853 --> 09:56.508
Lotta silence out there.
Must be good news, huh?

09:56.552 --> 09:59.642
♪♪

09:59.686 --> 10:01.905
Amelia: CT's negative,
labs look good.

10:01.949 --> 10:03.254
She has no history
of seizures?

10:03.298 --> 10:04.516
You don't think I would
have told you if there's

10:04.560 --> 10:05.648
a history of seizures?

10:05.692 --> 10:06.344
Mm. No family history?

10:06.388 --> 10:07.868
Same answer.

10:07.911 --> 10:09.826
Okay, but it is my job
to ask the questions.

10:09.870 --> 10:13.090
No, I get that, but maybe just
ask smarter questions.

10:13.134 --> 10:15.136
Are you okay?No, I'm not the patient.

10:15.179 --> 10:17.094
Ask smarter questions
about my patient.

10:17.138 --> 10:19.401
Addie --
No. Just no, no, no.

10:19.444 --> 10:22.273
I'm Dr. Montgomery.
You're Dr. Shepherd.

10:22.317 --> 10:24.406
And we are fixing this woman
who's lost so many pregnancies

10:24.449 --> 10:25.581
and then lost her husband.

10:25.625 --> 10:26.887
We are fixing this woman

10:26.930 --> 10:28.628
whose sisters
literally begged her

10:28.671 --> 10:30.368
not to participate
in my clinical trial

10:30.412 --> 10:32.762
because they were so afraid
of losing her, too.

10:32.806 --> 10:36.853
We are fixing this woman,
Dr. Shepherd.

10:36.897 --> 10:38.115
And, ideally,
we are going to fix her

10:38.159 --> 10:39.856
without having to
remove the donor uterus,

10:39.900 --> 10:42.598
setting my study
all the way back.

10:42.642 --> 10:44.078
[ Monitor beeping,
respirator hissing ]

10:44.121 --> 10:47.168
Okay, Dr. Montgomery.
I need an MRI.

10:47.211 --> 10:49.866
Um, because she was in status,
let's get an EEG.

10:49.910 --> 10:51.955
And re-run her
electrolyte panel

10:51.999 --> 10:53.391
and her immunosuppressant
levels.

10:53.435 --> 10:55.350
That sounds like
an excellent plan.

10:55.393 --> 10:56.830
Mm-hmm.

10:58.092 --> 10:59.397
Hi.

10:59.441 --> 11:00.964
Back so soon?

11:01.008 --> 11:03.401
Uh, that patient I told you
about -- he's here.

11:03.445 --> 11:04.664
Exam Room 4.

11:04.707 --> 11:06.056
That was fast.

11:06.100 --> 11:08.493
A little too fast.

11:08.537 --> 11:10.495
But just make sure you talk
to him like a doctor.

11:10.539 --> 11:12.019
I ama doctor.

11:12.062 --> 11:13.716
Be straight with him --
with both of us, okay?

11:13.760 --> 11:14.717
Okay.

11:16.371 --> 11:20.027
Dr. Hayes,
this is my son, Farouk.

11:20.070 --> 11:21.768
Hi.

11:21.811 --> 11:25.249
♪♪

11:31.081 --> 11:33.083
Mm.

11:34.215 --> 11:36.260
Hm.Meredith: Are you...

11:36.304 --> 11:37.479
Praying. Yes.

11:37.522 --> 11:38.741
[ Breathes deeply ]

11:38.785 --> 11:41.048
It's going to be okay,
Bailey.

11:41.091 --> 11:43.050
These are human beings.

11:43.093 --> 11:46.618
These are human beings
with children and parents

11:46.662 --> 11:48.011
and sisters and brothers.

11:48.055 --> 11:50.622
And we're putting
their bodies, their lives

11:50.666 --> 11:52.624
in the hands of...
children.

11:52.668 --> 11:54.235
But they're notchildren.

11:54.278 --> 11:56.933
But they look like children...
with scalpels.

11:56.977 --> 11:59.719
Well, so did we once.

11:59.762 --> 12:01.546
♪ One time Mnh-mnh.

12:01.590 --> 12:03.461
♪ Oh, yeah

12:03.505 --> 12:05.681
♪ Two times

12:05.725 --> 12:07.378
You've done
this before, right?

12:07.422 --> 12:08.423
In Pakistan?

12:08.466 --> 12:10.251
Years ago.
Many years ago.

12:10.294 --> 12:11.121
Scalpel.

12:11.165 --> 12:12.732
♪ It make me wanna dance

12:12.775 --> 12:14.472
♪ Big sound

12:14.516 --> 12:16.648
♪ In my system

12:16.692 --> 12:17.737
♪ Four times

12:17.780 --> 12:19.651
♪ Is a rebellion

12:19.695 --> 12:20.696
♪ Sweetie make me happy

12:20.740 --> 12:21.697
What are you doing?

12:21.741 --> 12:23.351
I saw Shepherd do it once.

12:23.394 --> 12:25.266
♪ Oh, yeah, oh, yeah
oh, yeah, oh, yeah ♪

12:25.309 --> 12:26.963
Scalpel.

12:27.007 --> 12:28.095
♪ Searchin' for some lovin'

12:28.138 --> 12:29.009
♪ Don't you worry
'cause I'm here ♪

12:29.052 --> 12:30.271
Scalpel.

12:30.314 --> 12:31.794
♪ You're my

12:31.838 --> 12:33.491
♪ One in a million

12:33.535 --> 12:34.971
♪ Oh

12:35.015 --> 12:36.799
♪ Are you ready?

12:36.843 --> 12:39.497
♪ Are you ready for some fun?

12:39.541 --> 12:41.804
♪ Oh, na, yeah

12:41.848 --> 12:43.632
♪ Are you ready?

12:43.675 --> 12:44.764
♪ We can't stop

12:44.807 --> 12:46.548
♪ We've only just begun

12:46.591 --> 12:47.679
♪ Oh, yeah

12:47.723 --> 12:49.812
♪ Ooo

12:49.856 --> 12:52.336
♪ I show you somethin' new

12:52.380 --> 12:53.511
♪ Hey

12:53.555 --> 12:56.776
♪ I'm gonna make you move

12:56.819 --> 12:58.560
♪ I show you something

12:58.603 --> 12:59.822
♪ You're my

12:59.866 --> 13:01.519
♪ One in a million

13:01.563 --> 13:02.912
♪ Ooo

13:02.956 --> 13:04.653
♪ Are you ready?

13:04.696 --> 13:05.785
♪ We can't stop

13:05.828 --> 13:07.917
♪ We've only just begun

13:07.961 --> 13:09.049
♪ Oh, yeah

13:09.092 --> 13:10.702
♪ Ooo

13:10.746 --> 13:13.531
♪ I show you something new

13:13.575 --> 13:14.663
♪ Hey

13:14.706 --> 13:17.579
♪ I'm gonna make you move

13:19.233 --> 13:20.712
Hey, Doctor.

13:20.756 --> 13:23.063
Um, can you give this
to Niki?

13:23.106 --> 13:26.370
She asked me to charge it,
and so it's charged.

13:26.414 --> 13:27.719
Here.

13:27.763 --> 13:30.635
Oh, come on.
You're leaving?

13:30.679 --> 13:32.768
You can't just hold her hand
for a few hours

13:32.812 --> 13:33.900
so she doesn't
give birth alone?

13:33.943 --> 13:36.946
We matched
online a month ago.

13:36.990 --> 13:39.731
I'm not a bad guy.
I work at the Post Office.[ Sighs ]

13:39.775 --> 13:42.212
I live in a studio apartment.
I'm not ready to be a dad.

13:43.518 --> 13:45.433
And she lied to me.

13:45.476 --> 13:49.872
I mean, don't you think this
is a pretty big lie?

13:49.916 --> 13:51.700
Just give me the phone.
[ Sighs ]

13:51.743 --> 13:53.223
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

13:53.267 --> 13:55.486
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

14:02.319 --> 14:03.277
Okay.

14:03.320 --> 14:04.582
Um...

14:04.626 --> 14:05.888
[ Clears throat ]

14:07.368 --> 14:10.806
Farouk's EKG shows
nonspecific ST changes.

14:10.850 --> 14:12.155
And I hear
a concerning murmur.

14:12.199 --> 14:14.157
So I'm not losing
my mind.

14:14.201 --> 14:15.376
No.

14:15.419 --> 14:16.856
[ Sighs ]

14:19.380 --> 14:20.555
Is there anything
I should know

14:20.598 --> 14:22.209
about Farouk's
medical history?

14:22.252 --> 14:24.211
He used to get a lot
of ear infections.

14:24.254 --> 14:27.301
[ Chuckles ]
He once fell off his bike

14:27.344 --> 14:29.564
and knocked out his two front
teeth, and it was just -- Right.

14:29.607 --> 14:31.218
Not relevant.

14:31.261 --> 14:34.134
He was treated for TB about
10 years ago in Iraq.

14:34.177 --> 14:36.614
I don't know anything about the
first four years of his life.

14:36.658 --> 14:37.833
Iraq.
That's where he grew up?

14:37.877 --> 14:39.313
He was born in Syria,

14:39.356 --> 14:40.923
but he came to Iraq
as a refugee

14:40.967 --> 14:42.185
after his parents died.

14:42.229 --> 14:45.580
I raised him while
I was being held as a POW

14:45.623 --> 14:47.930
and, you know,
getting my abs exploded.

14:47.974 --> 14:49.801
You and your brother
both served.

14:49.845 --> 14:51.107
I didn't realize.

14:51.151 --> 14:52.674
How would you?

14:53.980 --> 14:55.198
I want to do an echo.

14:55.242 --> 14:56.983
Do it. Do it all.

14:57.026 --> 14:59.899
Uh, Hayes,
and do you mind

14:59.942 --> 15:02.075
just keeping this
between us for now?

15:02.118 --> 15:04.207
If Owen finds out about this,
he'll freak out,

15:04.251 --> 15:05.948
and I'm already
freaking out a little bit.

15:05.992 --> 15:07.471
I've been there.[ Breathes sharply ]

15:07.515 --> 15:09.778
Of course.
Thank you.

15:09.821 --> 15:11.649
[ Conversations continue ]

15:11.693 --> 15:13.347
[ Child babbling in distance ]

15:13.390 --> 15:15.175
[ Conversations continue ]

15:16.263 --> 15:18.091
Owen: Hey there, Roy.

15:18.134 --> 15:21.398
Roy: Well, you two gonna tell me
what you saw on those scans?

15:21.442 --> 15:23.705
My ex-wife looks happier
to see me than you two.

15:23.748 --> 15:25.272
[ Laughter ]

15:25.315 --> 15:26.751
Noah, you mind
giving us a minute?

15:26.795 --> 15:28.928
No, it's okay, Doc.
He -- He -- He can stay.

15:28.971 --> 15:30.320
[ Clears throat ]

15:31.713 --> 15:35.282
Roy, there was an abnormality
in a section of your lung,

15:35.325 --> 15:37.153
and it looks like it's
an early stage of cancer.

15:37.197 --> 15:39.199
Early.

15:39.242 --> 15:41.201
Doesn't sound so bad.

15:41.244 --> 15:43.072
Well, with cancer,
the usual surgical treatment

15:43.116 --> 15:44.334
would be a lobectomy.

15:44.378 --> 15:45.988
We'd take out
that entire section.

15:46.032 --> 15:47.903
But with fibrosis
this advanced,

15:47.947 --> 15:49.731
you can't afford to
give up

15:49.774 --> 15:51.254
that much
of your lung function.

15:51.298 --> 15:52.952
Well, I didn't exactly
think I had a whole decade

15:52.995 --> 15:53.953
in front of me.

15:53.996 --> 15:55.824
[ Clicks tongue ]

15:55.867 --> 15:56.999
So, what're we talking?
[ Coughs ]

15:57.043 --> 15:58.261
A couple years?

15:58.305 --> 15:59.523
Sooner?

15:59.567 --> 16:01.482
[ Coughs ] Hmm?

16:01.525 --> 16:04.485
What can you do to get me
to Congress next month?

16:04.528 --> 16:06.095
Well, we could try
a segmentectomy,

16:06.139 --> 16:08.315
where we'd just remove
the mass.

16:08.358 --> 16:11.144
It's very risky, though.[ Coughs ]

16:11.187 --> 16:13.798
Honestly, I don't know
that I'd recommend it.

16:13.842 --> 16:16.932
But it could buy me
some more time, yeah?

16:16.976 --> 16:19.587
Possibly. A little.

16:19.630 --> 16:21.763
Well, let -- let's do it.
Slice me open.

16:21.806 --> 16:23.330
Roy, no.

16:23.373 --> 16:25.854
Send somebody else
to Washington.

16:25.897 --> 16:28.291
Hey, if I collapse
while I'm there,

16:28.335 --> 16:31.599
it might help our case,
right? [ Coughs ]

16:31.642 --> 16:33.340
It's fine.

16:33.383 --> 16:35.211
I have
a little cancer, yeah?

16:35.255 --> 16:37.779
I've spent
my entire career --

16:37.822 --> 16:41.826
hell, my entire life--
fighting.

16:41.870 --> 16:43.611
Why would I stop now?

16:43.654 --> 16:45.656
I want the surgery.

16:46.527 --> 16:48.355
Okay.

16:48.398 --> 16:49.747
[ Machinery whirring ]

16:53.099 --> 16:55.884
Tell me why you
left Scout's dad.

16:55.927 --> 16:57.146
I already told you.

16:57.190 --> 16:58.756
No, you told me you said no
to his proposal,

16:58.800 --> 17:00.541
but you didn't
tell me why.

17:00.584 --> 17:04.414
Uh. Well, everything about it
was a disaster.

17:04.458 --> 17:07.330
I mean, it felt gaslighty
and manipulative

17:07.374 --> 17:10.464
that he did it
at Maggie's wedding,

17:10.507 --> 17:12.509
using Mer's kids as props.

17:12.553 --> 17:15.686
Is he a gaslighty and
manipulative guy as a rule?

17:15.730 --> 17:17.427
No.

17:17.471 --> 17:19.777
Because, you know, the other way
you could see that proposal

17:19.821 --> 17:22.911
is that he was being
incredibly earnest and romantic.

17:22.954 --> 17:24.173
I mean,
if you were a person

17:24.217 --> 17:27.307
who saw the world through
rose-colored glasses,

17:27.350 --> 17:30.179
you know, like people in --
in love do.

17:30.223 --> 17:31.615
Okay, I want to go back
to pretending

17:31.659 --> 17:33.052
we don't know each other.

17:33.095 --> 17:34.401
And we'll do that when
the films are up.

17:34.444 --> 17:35.880
How come you get to
make all the rules?

17:35.924 --> 17:37.230
Because I'm older
and because my patient

17:37.273 --> 17:39.101
might be brain-damaged,
and I need to be distracted.

17:39.145 --> 17:41.538
So tell me why
you said no.

17:41.582 --> 17:44.063
Um...
[ Sighs ]

17:44.106 --> 17:46.326
I knew for months that
I didn't want what he wanted.

17:46.369 --> 17:49.155
We had Scout,
and we had Mer's kids

17:49.198 --> 17:51.070
because she was
in the hospital with --

17:51.113 --> 17:53.724
I heard. I prayed.
Yeah.

17:53.768 --> 17:56.249
So we were drowning
in children and domesticity,

17:56.292 --> 18:00.166
and every day, I felt like
I might die of it.

18:00.209 --> 18:01.210
[ Sighs ]

18:01.254 --> 18:03.256
I love all the kids,
but every day,

18:03.299 --> 18:06.389
I thought I might die
of monotony and boredom

18:06.433 --> 18:09.088
and dirty diapers
and dirty dishes and laundry.

18:09.131 --> 18:12.091
And every day,
I thought about doing drugs.

18:12.134 --> 18:15.790
And every night,
I went to virtual meetings.

18:15.833 --> 18:17.661
And I am here
to tell you that

18:17.705 --> 18:19.054
those virtual meetings...
[ Clears throat ]

18:19.098 --> 18:20.577
...while better
than no meetings,

18:20.621 --> 18:23.624
are no substitute for
regular in-person meetings.

18:23.667 --> 18:24.668
They're not the same.

18:24.712 --> 18:27.018
And, so, I was hanging
by a thread,

18:27.062 --> 18:32.415
and, um, Link...wasn't.

18:32.459 --> 18:35.679
He was falling in love
with domesticity.

18:35.723 --> 18:38.856
And he was
the world's most stand-up guy.

18:38.900 --> 18:42.860
And he started proposing
all the time,

18:42.904 --> 18:45.080
despite me saying no.

18:45.124 --> 18:47.256
And he decided that
he wanted more kids,

18:47.300 --> 18:49.563
and I felt like
I couldn't breathe.

18:49.606 --> 18:52.957
And, um, then I judged
myself for that,

18:53.001 --> 18:57.092
like I think
you are judging me now.

18:57.136 --> 18:59.181
During the pandemic,
I drank so much red wine,

18:59.225 --> 19:01.444
I seriously considered
checking myself into rehab.

19:01.488 --> 19:03.185
Really?
Addison: Really.

19:03.229 --> 19:05.231
I looked
like a swollen tick.

19:05.274 --> 19:07.102
[ Both laugh ]

19:07.146 --> 19:08.799
I lost it.

19:08.843 --> 19:10.323
Lost it.

19:10.366 --> 19:12.934
I just hated -- hated --
being stuck at home.

19:12.977 --> 19:14.109
You know,
some people loved it.

19:14.153 --> 19:16.198
They baked bread.
I don't like bread.

19:16.242 --> 19:22.204
I began to truly hate
my video-game-obsessed son

19:22.248 --> 19:24.293
and my husband,
who, by the way,

19:24.337 --> 19:27.557
took up a model-train hobby that
seemed to truly delight him.

19:27.601 --> 19:28.993
No.
Exactly.

19:29.037 --> 19:30.212
Mm.

19:30.256 --> 19:35.348
Yeah, I um -- I went
really dark, Amelia.

19:35.391 --> 19:39.221
I had
dark, dark thoughts.

19:39.265 --> 19:42.355
I was daydreaming about going to
sleep and never waking up,

19:42.398 --> 19:47.186
and that thought...
comforted me.

19:48.622 --> 19:50.363
I hate that for you.

19:50.406 --> 19:52.016
[ Sniffles ]

19:52.060 --> 19:53.757
And thank you.

19:53.801 --> 19:55.455
Thank you.

19:55.498 --> 19:58.632
Because...me too.

19:58.675 --> 20:00.982
[ Beeping ]

20:01.025 --> 20:02.462
Films are up,
Dr. Shepherd.

20:02.505 --> 20:03.985
[ Clears throat ]

20:04.028 --> 20:05.029
♪♪

20:10.905 --> 20:13.821
Venting the ports.

20:13.864 --> 20:15.605
[ Monitor beeping,
ventilator hissing ]

20:15.649 --> 20:17.216
You're already finished?

20:17.259 --> 20:18.782
Yeah.
Is that bad?

20:18.826 --> 20:20.741
Oh, gosh.
Did I forget something?

20:20.784 --> 20:22.133
No, no, no.
It's -- It's --

20:22.177 --> 20:24.658
We just got one more
lap chole through the ER.

20:24.701 --> 20:26.312
You're making
excellent time.

20:26.355 --> 20:27.835
How's about
a double feature, Schmitt?

20:27.878 --> 20:29.532
Hell yeah.

20:30.664 --> 20:33.057
Dr. Webber, sir.

20:33.101 --> 20:34.711
That's what
I'm talking about.

20:34.755 --> 20:36.365
Your patient
will be in OR 7.

20:36.409 --> 20:37.714
Khan, you'll assist.

20:37.758 --> 20:40.848
[ Monitor beeping,
respirator hissing ]

20:40.891 --> 20:43.677
[ Singsong voice ]
We got two lap choles!

20:43.720 --> 20:45.287
We got two lap choles!

20:45.331 --> 20:47.289
Yes, we did!
[ Laughs ]

20:48.899 --> 20:50.597
0 Vicryl, please.

20:53.469 --> 20:54.514
Looking good, brother.

20:54.557 --> 20:55.863
-[ Coughs ]
-Okay.

20:55.906 --> 20:57.647
Whoa! Looks like you have
some visitors, Roy.

20:57.691 --> 20:59.301
Eh, just
a few familiar faces.

20:59.345 --> 21:00.868
Look at this
sorry lot, huh?

21:00.911 --> 21:02.826
[ Laughter ]

21:02.870 --> 21:05.220
Eh, Noah shouldn't have
bothered you all.

21:05.264 --> 21:06.961
Well, you knew we had to get
our last licks in

21:07.004 --> 21:08.441
before you went under
the knife.Ah, yeah.

21:08.484 --> 21:10.486
Listen, if I don't
make it out of there --

21:10.530 --> 21:12.793
Will you shut up?
Of course you'll make it.

21:12.836 --> 21:14.360
[ Laughs ]You know, at our base,

21:14.403 --> 21:16.013
the guys from the Afghan army
would bring chickens

21:16.057 --> 21:17.188
and cook them for us.

21:17.232 --> 21:19.408
Well, one day,
they brought a live sheep.

21:19.452 --> 21:20.975
Remember this?

21:21.018 --> 21:22.498
And Roy insisted on
helping out.

21:22.542 --> 21:25.022
Told 'em he'd, uh, butchered
pigs before or some lie.

21:25.066 --> 21:26.154
[ Laughs, coughs ]

21:26.197 --> 21:27.460
I stand by that lie.

21:27.503 --> 21:28.678
[ Laughter ]

21:28.722 --> 21:30.637
And this sheep -- well,
he did not like Roy.

21:30.680 --> 21:32.073
The second he got near him,
he got kicked in the head,

21:32.116 --> 21:33.379
knocked on his ass,
and trampled.

21:33.422 --> 21:34.684
[ Laughter ]

21:34.728 --> 21:35.424
What happened
to the sheep?

21:35.468 --> 21:36.947
Well, he took off,

21:36.991 --> 21:38.471
left Roy on the ground,
bloody and bruised.

21:38.514 --> 21:39.646
That's gotta hurt.

21:39.689 --> 21:41.952
So I run over,
and Roy is out cold.

21:41.996 --> 21:45.260
And just when I start to panic,
his crazy eyes fly open.

21:45.304 --> 21:48.350
He jumps up, screaming,
"Yeehaw!"

21:48.394 --> 21:50.396
And he takes off
after that sheep.

21:50.439 --> 21:52.267
I have no memory of that.
I -- I --

21:52.311 --> 21:54.878
[ Coughs ] Probably
because of the concussion.

21:54.922 --> 21:56.880
Point is, if that angry sheep
can't get rid of you,

21:56.924 --> 21:58.273
nothing can.

21:58.317 --> 22:00.362
[ Coughs, groans ]

22:00.406 --> 22:01.450
Pbht.

22:01.494 --> 22:02.886
[ Grunting ]

22:02.930 --> 22:04.758
♪♪

22:04.801 --> 22:05.759
Okay.

22:05.802 --> 22:08.588
You guys,
I won't forget this.

22:10.372 --> 22:12.331
You all coming here for me.

22:12.374 --> 22:14.202
♪♪

22:14.245 --> 22:15.464
We ready?

22:15.508 --> 22:16.683
We're ready.

22:16.726 --> 22:18.206
Go.
Yeah.

22:18.249 --> 22:19.076
Man: We got your six.

22:19.120 --> 22:20.339
Alright, brother.

22:20.382 --> 22:22.297
You got this,
brother.

22:22.341 --> 22:23.690
Get 'em, Roy.

22:23.733 --> 22:25.909
♪♪

22:25.953 --> 22:28.259
Jo: Niki, your
EKG looks normal,

22:28.303 --> 22:30.349
and cardio couldn't
see anything on your echo.

22:30.392 --> 22:33.395
So is it possible that you're
experiencing a little anxiety?

22:33.439 --> 22:34.657
Niki: Is it possible?!

22:34.701 --> 22:36.398
I'm having a baby,
and, somehow,

22:36.442 --> 22:38.531
my new boyfriend didn't
notice I was pregnant.

22:38.574 --> 22:39.923
Of course it is possible.

22:39.967 --> 22:41.360
[ Groans ]

22:41.403 --> 22:43.884
Where is Dustin with
those ice chips?

22:43.927 --> 22:45.625
What is important
right now

22:45.668 --> 22:47.104
is that you take some
deep breaths

22:47.148 --> 22:48.497
and stay calm, okay?

22:49.629 --> 22:51.500
He left, didn't he?

22:51.544 --> 22:53.589
[ Sighs ]

22:53.633 --> 22:54.677
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm all alone.

22:54.721 --> 22:56.244
I can't do this all alone.

22:56.287 --> 22:58.507
Yes, you can.
I know you can.

22:58.551 --> 23:00.248
All my friends
thought I was crazy

23:00.291 --> 23:02.381
for having
some random guy's baby.

23:02.424 --> 23:04.644
And my parents told me
they wanted no part of it.

23:04.687 --> 23:06.994
[ Crying ] So I moved
across the country.

23:07.037 --> 23:10.345
And I was
lonely and scared.

23:10.389 --> 23:14.915
And then I met Dustin,
and he didn't seem to mind.

23:14.958 --> 23:16.786
How did he not notice?

23:16.830 --> 23:18.962
I don't know, Niki.

23:19.006 --> 23:20.921
But -- But you wanted
to have this baby,

23:20.964 --> 23:23.184
and you are about
to meet him.

23:23.227 --> 23:26.143
I just wanted someone
to hold my hand.

23:26.187 --> 23:27.536
I'll hold your hand.

23:28.972 --> 23:32.062
[ Both laugh ]

23:32.106 --> 23:34.195
Who's gonna
deliver the baby?

23:34.238 --> 23:37.067
Um, hey, uh, can you page
Dr. DeLuca, please?

23:37.111 --> 23:38.808
Now.

23:38.852 --> 23:40.854
Here we go.
[ Sniffles ]

23:40.897 --> 23:43.987
We almost have the critical
view of safety cleared.

23:44.031 --> 23:46.207
Are we ready
to move forward?

23:46.250 --> 23:48.165
[ Monitor beeping,
respirator hissing ]

23:49.428 --> 23:50.646
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]The field is filling with blood.

23:50.690 --> 23:52.343
Why is the field
filling with blood?

23:52.387 --> 23:53.954
Maybe you
should suction.

23:53.997 --> 23:55.521
But you're my assist.
Maybe youshould suction!

23:55.564 --> 23:58.219
Okay, uh, indications to convert
to open cholecystectomy --

23:58.262 --> 24:00.264
adhesions, fibrosis,
unclear anatomy, hemorrhage.

24:00.308 --> 24:02.789
This could be the cystic artery,
the hepatic artery...

24:02.832 --> 24:03.572
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

24:03.616 --> 24:04.704
We have to open her up.

24:04.747 --> 24:05.966
We?Get the trocars out.

24:06.009 --> 24:07.794
And somebody
call an attending.

24:07.837 --> 24:09.491
[ Rapid beeping continues ]

24:09.535 --> 24:11.101
Okay, the good news is,

24:11.145 --> 24:12.973
there's no sign of CVA,
edema, or tumor.

24:13.016 --> 24:15.932
And there's no electrolyte
abnormalities or infection.

24:15.976 --> 24:17.325
Okay, well, that's good news
and bad news.

24:17.368 --> 24:19.066
Why?

24:19.109 --> 24:20.371
Because with everything
else ruled out,

24:20.415 --> 24:21.808
it's likely that
the seizures are being caused

24:21.851 --> 24:23.505
by neurotoxicity
from anti-rejection meds.

24:23.549 --> 24:24.898
Damn it. Damn it!

24:24.941 --> 24:26.552
We can switch her
immunosuppressants

24:26.595 --> 24:28.858
and keep her on anticonvulsants
and watch her like a hawk.

24:28.902 --> 24:30.469
I live in
Los Angeles, okay?

24:30.512 --> 24:31.687
And as much
as I hated them

24:31.731 --> 24:32.906
when I was trapped
in a house with them,

24:32.949 --> 24:34.473
I do love
my son and my husband.

24:34.516 --> 24:35.996
I have to get
back home to them.

24:36.039 --> 24:38.912
I mean, I-I had arranged
for the clinical-trial team

24:38.955 --> 24:40.870
to monitor her
from here on out.

24:40.914 --> 24:42.132
I can, too.

24:42.176 --> 24:43.482
Oh, I can't because
I'm going back and forth

24:43.525 --> 24:44.700
to Minnesota.

24:44.744 --> 24:46.093
But Bailey can
or s-someone can.

24:46.136 --> 24:47.094
[ Sighs ]

24:47.137 --> 24:48.574
What I'm saying is,
we can help.

24:48.617 --> 24:50.271
You'll just have to share
credit when you publish.

24:50.314 --> 24:53.100
Don't say that like
it's a small thing.

24:53.143 --> 24:56.016
I mean, it's risky.
She's had so many seizures.

24:56.059 --> 24:57.757
If she seizes up again,
I --[ Door closes ]

24:57.800 --> 24:59.323
Well, we've loaded her
with anticonvulsants.

24:59.367 --> 25:00.847
We will watch
her closely.

25:00.890 --> 25:03.153
If we have to take out the
uterus, we take out the uterus.

25:03.197 --> 25:05.460
But let's cross that bridge
when we come to it.

25:07.767 --> 25:10.291
I want
to agree with you.

25:10.334 --> 25:11.988
Okay, so what's
stopping you?

25:12.032 --> 25:14.774
I need to not kill
this patient.

25:14.817 --> 25:17.951
I need to not
let her die.

25:17.994 --> 25:21.563
And -- And helping her
helped me.

25:21.607 --> 25:23.217
It excited me.
A uterine transplant?

25:23.260 --> 25:24.958
I mean, the thought of
creating something for her

25:25.001 --> 25:27.090
that didn't exist
before her

25:27.134 --> 25:30.877
made me want to get out of bed
in the morning.

25:30.920 --> 25:33.532
But I don't want to make
a decision that's selfish.

25:33.575 --> 25:36.796
I need to prioritize her life
over the study.

25:36.839 --> 25:39.233
And I need you to tell me

25:39.276 --> 25:41.627
if there's a chance
that you think I'm not.

25:41.670 --> 25:46.501
Dr. Montgomery, your patient
was so in love with her husband

25:46.545 --> 25:50.331
that she is having a baby
with him even though he is dead.

25:50.374 --> 25:53.116
She's so in love with the idea
of becoming a mother

25:53.160 --> 25:54.944
that she entered your study

25:54.988 --> 25:57.730
knowing that she was
risking her life.

25:57.773 --> 25:59.166
You are not
being selfish.

25:59.209 --> 26:02.952
You are doing
every single thing you can

26:02.996 --> 26:04.345
to help her
live her dream.

26:04.388 --> 26:07.609
And that is
an excellent reason

26:07.653 --> 26:09.306
to get out of bed
in the morning.

26:09.350 --> 26:12.048
♪♪

26:12.092 --> 26:13.615
We're almost
ready here, Roy.

26:13.659 --> 26:15.574
Are you sure you still want to
go through with this?

26:15.617 --> 26:17.358
[ Groans ]

26:17.401 --> 26:19.708
I got a daughter.

26:19.752 --> 26:23.669
She lives on the East Coast
with her husband, two kids.

26:23.712 --> 26:25.671
I don't ever see them.

26:25.714 --> 26:26.933
She took her mother's side
in the divorce,

26:26.976 --> 26:28.717
and that -- that was it.

26:28.761 --> 26:31.241
But if someone
had done this to her,

26:31.285 --> 26:33.809
if someone had made her
breathe in that crap

26:33.853 --> 26:35.724
and caused her
a lifetime of pain,

26:35.768 --> 26:37.552
I'd want that person dead.

26:37.596 --> 26:39.902
Roy, we're going to
stop this.

26:39.946 --> 26:43.645
We're going to hold the people
at fault responsible, okay?

26:43.689 --> 26:45.691
I'mresponsible.

26:46.692 --> 26:48.476
I'm not sure
I understand.

26:48.519 --> 26:50.696
I authorized it.

26:50.739 --> 26:53.046
The burn pit on our base.

26:53.089 --> 26:54.351
Trash was piling up.

26:54.395 --> 26:57.311
There was no plumbing,
no sewage system.

26:57.354 --> 27:00.401
And it's not like the garbageman
comes on Tuesdays. I --

27:00.444 --> 27:03.491
[ Coughing ] I heard the, uh,
other bases were burning it all.

27:03.534 --> 27:05.232
[ Coughs, sniffs ]

27:05.275 --> 27:09.540
So...that's what
I told them to do.

27:11.499 --> 27:13.153
I didn't invent the idea...

27:13.196 --> 27:14.371
[ Coughs ]

27:14.415 --> 27:16.417
...but when I close my eyes
at night,

27:16.460 --> 27:18.898
I see that black smoke
billowing up from the ground,

27:18.941 --> 27:23.946
and I know that I committed
the worst crime...

27:26.035 --> 27:27.689
...complicity.

27:27.733 --> 27:29.430
♪♪

27:29.473 --> 27:31.214
[ Sniffles ]

27:31.258 --> 27:35.262
So, at the end of the day,
I might deserve to die.

27:35.958 --> 27:39.005
Everyone else deserves to live.

27:39.048 --> 27:41.224
Let's do it.

27:41.268 --> 27:43.139
Let's go.

27:44.401 --> 27:46.621
[ Whooshing ]

27:46.665 --> 27:48.014
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

27:48.057 --> 27:49.493
What happened?I-I don't know.

27:49.537 --> 27:51.104
The field filled with blood,
and now I converted to open.

27:51.147 --> 27:52.540
And now --
Well,
you should have waited.

27:52.583 --> 27:54.411
She was bleeding out.You still should have waited.

27:54.455 --> 27:56.109
I'm sorry, Chief, but --Step aside.

27:56.152 --> 27:58.851
Okay, I need another suction
and I need laps now.

27:58.894 --> 28:00.156
What can I do?

28:00.200 --> 28:02.332
If you want this patient
to live, step aside.

28:02.376 --> 28:03.725
Okay.

28:03.769 --> 28:05.640
Okay, suction.

28:05.684 --> 28:06.685
Okay, clamp.

28:12.516 --> 28:15.041
Owen: I have never seen
lung tissue like this. You?

28:15.084 --> 28:16.520
I have -- in advanced ARDS,
secondary to COVID.

28:16.564 --> 28:19.132
And it didn't end well.
Suction.

28:19.175 --> 28:21.482
[ Sighs ] The tissue's just
falling apart in my hands.

28:21.525 --> 28:22.962
Stapler.

28:23.005 --> 28:24.180
Thanks.

28:24.224 --> 28:25.225
[ Suction gurgling ]

28:25.268 --> 28:26.705
Okay.

28:26.748 --> 28:28.576
Thank you for doing this.

28:28.619 --> 28:30.317
I know you didn't think
it was a good idea.

28:30.360 --> 28:32.667
No, I didn't, but I believe
in fighting for what's right,

28:32.711 --> 28:34.234
and if giving this guy
a few more months

28:34.277 --> 28:36.453
helps make life better
for others, I'm in.

28:36.497 --> 28:39.326
Okay. Alright.

28:39.369 --> 28:40.631
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

28:40.675 --> 28:42.155
He's hemorrhaging.

28:42.198 --> 28:43.199
Hold pressure.
I'll try to find the source.

28:43.243 --> 28:45.245
Yep.DeBakey clamp -- now!

28:47.029 --> 28:48.857
Yeah, yeah.
Come on.

28:48.901 --> 28:50.032
Come on.

28:50.076 --> 28:51.468
There. Got it.[ Rapid beeping stops ]

28:51.512 --> 28:52.861
[ Breathes deeply ]

28:52.905 --> 28:55.211
Alright. So, that's how this
is gonna go, huh, Roy?

28:55.255 --> 28:57.170
[ Chuckles ] I've only known
this guy for eight hours.

28:57.213 --> 28:59.433
I'm pretty sure he's not
going to make it easy on us.

28:59.476 --> 29:01.391
I operated in Boston
for 15 years.

29:01.435 --> 29:03.263
No patient
made it easy on me.

29:03.306 --> 29:04.568
Hemostats.

29:04.612 --> 29:07.223
[ Suction gurgling,
monitor beeping ]

29:07.267 --> 29:09.399
Finished.

29:09.443 --> 29:11.750
And that, ladies and gentlemen,
is how it's done.

29:11.793 --> 29:13.621
Yes, it is!

29:13.664 --> 29:15.405
[ Both laugh ]

29:15.449 --> 29:19.409
Flawless technique on not one,
but two lap choles today.

29:19.453 --> 29:21.455
Take notes if you want
to survive.

29:21.498 --> 29:24.327
Thank you, sir,
for the opportunity,

29:24.371 --> 29:26.677
the patients, the wis--You know,
by working together,

29:26.721 --> 29:29.376
we saved 13 patients
from cholecystitis --

29:29.419 --> 29:31.030
a hospital record.

29:31.073 --> 29:33.336
You should all be proud.
Now, study hard.

29:33.380 --> 29:34.816
Today was lap chole.

29:34.860 --> 29:36.122
Tomorrow, it could be
something more.

29:36.165 --> 29:38.559
Don't come unprepared.

29:38.602 --> 29:40.387
[ Cheers and applause] Yes!

29:40.430 --> 29:44.260
♪♪

29:44.304 --> 29:46.306
Hi, Tovah.

29:46.349 --> 29:48.569
I'm Dr. Shepherd.♪ Every little heartache

29:48.612 --> 29:51.659
Is it gone?
Did I -- Did I lose it?

29:51.702 --> 29:53.095
Did you take the uterus?

29:53.139 --> 29:54.401
No.

29:54.444 --> 29:56.577
But, Tovah...

29:56.620 --> 29:58.448
you didn't reject it.

29:58.492 --> 29:59.841
♪ When I was wasted

29:59.885 --> 30:00.886
Is there still
a chance?

30:00.929 --> 30:02.888
There's still a chance.

30:02.931 --> 30:04.715
We're gonna step up
your protocol,

30:04.759 --> 30:05.978
and you're still
in the trial.

30:06.021 --> 30:07.457
[ Crying ]
Oh, my God, thank you.

30:07.501 --> 30:08.937
♪ I mostly now forget

30:08.981 --> 30:10.547
Thank you. My God.
[ Sniffles ]

30:10.591 --> 30:11.897
♪ I flew all around the world

30:11.940 --> 30:13.681
I'm gonna do
a quick neuro check.

30:13.724 --> 30:16.771
Let just...
give her a minute to cry.

30:16.815 --> 30:19.121
♪ It was all the same

30:19.165 --> 30:20.601
♪ It was all a game [ Groans ]

30:20.644 --> 30:22.168
Wilson,
what are you doing?!

30:22.211 --> 30:23.865
She won't
let go of my hand!

30:23.909 --> 30:25.258
Okay, you're an OB.[ Door closes ]

30:25.301 --> 30:27.869
Your job is to deliver
the babies, not to hold hands.

30:27.913 --> 30:28.957
♪ So break my heart Okay.

30:29.001 --> 30:30.480
[ Groans ]

30:30.524 --> 30:31.742
A-And she's crowning.

30:31.786 --> 30:32.831
Niki, I need to help
get the baby out,

30:32.874 --> 30:33.919
but I will be
right over here.

30:33.962 --> 30:35.485
No, no, no.
No, I can't do this.

30:35.529 --> 30:37.052
I just can't.

30:37.096 --> 30:37.966
Niki, you're worried
about being alone.

30:38.010 --> 30:39.446
You're not alone.

30:39.489 --> 30:41.448
You have your son,
and as soon as he comes out,

30:41.491 --> 30:42.971
he will be
your whole heart.

30:43.015 --> 30:45.147
And it's hard,
and it's exhausting,

30:45.191 --> 30:47.497
and there are days when you will
turn around and wonder,

30:47.541 --> 30:48.672
"Where is this baby's mother?

30:48.716 --> 30:50.196
Because it absolutely
cannot be me."

30:50.239 --> 30:52.894
♪ Go on and break my heart

30:52.938 --> 30:54.678
But you will love him
so much,

30:54.722 --> 30:57.638
you'll let him sleep on you
anywhere, anytime,

30:57.681 --> 30:59.379
no matter how uncomfortable
you are.

30:59.422 --> 31:01.424
And just one smell of his head
will make you feel like

31:01.468 --> 31:03.165
your heart could explode.

31:03.209 --> 31:05.602
And that is worth so much more
than your fear.

31:05.646 --> 31:07.648
Okay?
You ready to start pushing?

31:07.691 --> 31:08.910
On the count of three.

31:08.954 --> 31:10.825
One, two, three.

31:10.869 --> 31:12.435
[ Groans, screams ]

31:12.479 --> 31:13.784
Push, push, push, push.

31:13.828 --> 31:14.916
Here's the head.Good.

31:14.960 --> 31:16.613
[ Groaning ]Wait, wait, wait.

31:16.657 --> 31:17.832
Niki, stop pushing.

31:17.876 --> 31:20.356
Okay, uh,
shoulder dystocia.

31:20.400 --> 31:22.141
Baby's shoulder is caught
behind the pubic bone.

31:22.184 --> 31:23.794
Okay, Wilson,
what do you do?

31:23.838 --> 31:26.449
Uh, we're doing a McRoberts
maneuver to get the baby out.

31:26.493 --> 31:27.494
Wait. A what?

31:27.537 --> 31:29.148
We've got you, Niki.

31:29.191 --> 31:30.149
♪ Every little heartache,
every little mistake ♪

31:30.192 --> 31:32.194
Alright.
We ready to push again?

31:32.238 --> 31:33.326
[ Crying ] Okay.Alright.

31:33.369 --> 31:35.763
One, two, three.

31:35.806 --> 31:38.113
Go.[ Groans, screams ]

31:38.157 --> 31:39.288
Okay, Wilson,
put your hand in and find

31:39.332 --> 31:40.507
the anterior
shoulder, okay?

31:40.550 --> 31:41.595
You got it?

31:41.638 --> 31:43.249
Yep.
Okay.

31:43.292 --> 31:45.729
Now push the back of the baby's
shoulder towards the chest.

31:45.773 --> 31:47.557
[ Groaning ]Gently.

31:47.601 --> 31:49.559
Okay.
[ Groans ]

31:49.603 --> 31:50.952
Here he comes.

31:50.996 --> 31:52.780
Oh, my goodness.

31:52.823 --> 31:54.129
You have a boy.

31:54.173 --> 31:55.826
Oh, my goodness.

31:55.870 --> 31:57.480
♪♪

31:57.524 --> 31:58.829
Well done, Wilson.

31:58.873 --> 32:01.832
♪ Into a thousand parts

32:01.876 --> 32:03.356
[ Baby crying ]

32:03.399 --> 32:09.884
♪♪

32:09.928 --> 32:12.017
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

32:16.456 --> 32:18.893
Farouk's echo
and cardiac MRI

32:18.937 --> 32:20.808
show constrictive
pericarditis.

32:20.851 --> 32:23.071
Most likely
secondary to the TB.
Hm.

32:23.115 --> 32:24.812
[ Sighs ] I'm so sorry.

32:24.855 --> 32:26.988
I-I wish it
was better news.

32:27.032 --> 32:28.859
He's already been through
so much,

32:28.903 --> 32:30.774
more than any kid should.
[ Scoffs ]

32:30.818 --> 32:32.820
And the hits
just keep coming.

32:36.650 --> 32:37.912
Do you want
to be alone?

32:37.956 --> 32:39.044
[ Crying ] I'm sorry.
I don't --

32:39.087 --> 32:40.959
I don't usually do this.
[ Sobs ]

32:41.002 --> 32:42.525
It's your son.
All bets are off.

32:42.569 --> 32:43.918
Mnh.

32:43.962 --> 32:45.354
[ Sniffles ]

32:45.398 --> 32:48.009
Uh, okay, so --
so what does this mean?

32:48.053 --> 32:50.664
Is he gonna need surgery or...
[ Sniffles ]

32:50.707 --> 32:52.927
I have to consult with cardio,
but I think so, yes.

32:52.971 --> 32:55.321
Most likely
a pericardiectomy.

32:55.364 --> 32:56.975
Oh, God.

32:57.018 --> 32:58.411
I'll admit him,
and we'll go from there.

32:58.454 --> 33:01.718
Oh, Farouk!
Oh, my God!

33:01.762 --> 33:05.853
God, he's so --
he's so good.

33:05.896 --> 33:08.987
I mean,
he's a teenager, but...

33:09.030 --> 33:11.728
God, he's just
always been such a good kid,

33:11.772 --> 33:16.429
despite what this
messed-up world has given him.

33:16.472 --> 33:18.431
He has to be okay.

33:18.474 --> 33:21.129
I will do everything in my power
to make sure that he is.

33:21.173 --> 33:22.174
That's a promise.

33:22.217 --> 33:24.089
Okay.

33:24.132 --> 33:25.351
Do you want me to
call your brother?

33:25.394 --> 33:27.092
I'll tell him,
just not yet.

33:27.135 --> 33:29.311
I...

33:29.355 --> 33:32.097
I-I need
to sit with this by myself

33:32.140 --> 33:33.315
for -- for a minute.

33:34.969 --> 33:36.362
Take all the time
you need.

33:36.405 --> 33:41.367
♪♪

33:41.410 --> 33:42.759
[ Sniffles ]

33:42.803 --> 33:44.674
♪♪

33:44.718 --> 33:46.981
So, his lungs had more scarring
than we expected.

33:47.025 --> 33:48.591
It's gonna be
a tough road ahead.

33:48.635 --> 33:50.332
Well, he can handle it.

33:50.376 --> 33:51.551
I know he can.

33:51.594 --> 33:54.119
[ Coughing ]

33:56.208 --> 33:57.383
[ Breathes sharply ]

33:57.426 --> 33:59.298
Thank you.

33:59.341 --> 34:00.734
Honestly, you're
the first doctor I've met

34:00.777 --> 34:02.083
who actually gave a crap,

34:02.127 --> 34:05.086
who's really done anything
for any of us.

34:05.130 --> 34:07.915
Well...I'm sorry
that's the case.

34:07.958 --> 34:11.092
But this is personal
to me, you know?

34:11.136 --> 34:14.617
I am in this with
all of you guys, okay?

34:14.661 --> 34:16.184
[ Monitor beeping ]

34:16.228 --> 34:17.751
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

34:17.794 --> 34:19.274
W-What's happening?

34:19.318 --> 34:21.146
Dr. Hunt!

34:21.189 --> 34:22.495
Noah, I'm gonna need you
to leave, okay?

34:22.538 --> 34:23.539
I'm not leaving him.

34:23.583 --> 34:26.064
Sergeant, step outside, now!

34:26.107 --> 34:28.109
Now!

34:28.153 --> 34:30.068
Winston: Damn it,
his O2 is plummeting.

34:30.111 --> 34:31.417
Noah, you got to go.

34:31.460 --> 34:32.635
Come on, Roy.

34:32.679 --> 34:34.115
V-fib! Paddles!

34:36.291 --> 34:38.076
Come on, Roy.Sir, you're
not allowed in here.

34:38.119 --> 34:38.989
Sir, you've got to go.Come on, Roy.

34:39.033 --> 34:40.513
Come on, Roy.
Hang in there!

34:40.556 --> 34:42.515
Okay,
let's charge to 120.

34:42.558 --> 34:43.864
Ready? And clear.

34:43.907 --> 34:44.908
[ Paddles thud ]

34:44.952 --> 34:46.301
No change.
Push 1 of epi.

34:46.345 --> 34:48.477
Charge to 150.
And...clear!

34:48.521 --> 34:49.478
[ Paddles thud ]

34:49.522 --> 34:50.827
Come on, Roy.

34:50.871 --> 34:51.959
200!

34:52.002 --> 34:52.829
And clear!

34:52.873 --> 34:53.961
[ Paddles thud ]

34:54.004 --> 34:55.876
♪♪

35:01.099 --> 35:03.362
Who wants cider?Congratulations, sweetheart.

35:03.405 --> 35:04.493
[ Laughing ] Ah.I know I was skeptical,

35:04.537 --> 35:07.279
but 13 lap choles,
that is something.

35:07.322 --> 35:08.715
[ Laughs ]Yes.

35:08.758 --> 35:11.370
Even though you did con me
into agreeing this morning.

35:11.413 --> 35:12.980
Con?
Mm-hmm.

35:13.023 --> 35:14.373
Is that what you're
calling it, what we did?

35:14.416 --> 35:15.374
Mm-hmm.

35:15.417 --> 35:16.723
[ Gasps ][ Laughs ]

35:16.766 --> 35:18.551
Well, you've set the bar
very high for yourself.

35:18.594 --> 35:21.467
The residents are going to
expect this all the time.Ohh.

35:21.510 --> 35:23.599
I mean, who knows?
The scrub nurses may walk out.

35:23.643 --> 35:25.601
[ Laughs ]Ah, well,
everyone will adapt.

35:25.645 --> 35:27.299
They'll have to,
because from now on,

35:27.342 --> 35:28.865
this is gonna be
my primary method of teaching.

35:28.909 --> 35:30.215
To the Webber Method.Yeah.

35:30.258 --> 35:31.564
Ooh! Rolls off the tongue,
doesn't it?

35:31.607 --> 35:33.479
Mm-hmm.[ Laughs ]

35:33.522 --> 35:35.263
Ah.
You still
don't like it.

35:35.307 --> 35:36.786
No, I don't.

35:36.830 --> 35:38.179
Look,
Helm clipped that artery

35:38.223 --> 35:40.138
with no attending
in the room.

35:40.181 --> 35:41.661
When I first walked in
and saw all that blood,

35:41.704 --> 35:42.966
even I didn't know
which way was up,

35:43.010 --> 35:44.533
so how was a resident
supposed to?

35:44.577 --> 35:46.796
You know as well as I
that complications

35:46.840 --> 35:48.363
could happened to --
to -- to any one of us.

35:48.407 --> 35:51.497
Which is why we owe it
to them and the patients

35:51.540 --> 35:55.196
to be there in the room.

35:55.240 --> 35:58.721
Bailey,
10 years from now,

35:58.765 --> 36:02.203
we are going to be short
tens of thousands of surgeons

36:02.247 --> 36:04.423
if we don't rethink
what we're doing here.

36:04.466 --> 36:07.208
We're a teaching hospital,
and we have a moral imperative

36:07.252 --> 36:08.992
to make sure that people
don't die because

36:09.036 --> 36:10.690
there's no one to
operate on them.

36:10.733 --> 36:12.779
That'swhat we owe
these patients.

36:12.822 --> 36:14.520
Meredith: Helm did prove
the system worked.

36:14.563 --> 36:15.782
She asked for help.

36:15.825 --> 36:17.653
She did exactly what
she was supposed to do.

36:17.697 --> 36:19.220
And you were there,
and you helped.

36:19.264 --> 36:21.222
The patient's alive
and stable and in recovery.

36:21.266 --> 36:22.745
It did work.

36:23.398 --> 36:25.792
[ Mumbling ] Oh, yeah.
To the Webber Method.

36:25.835 --> 36:27.097
No. I-I'm sorry.
What, now?

36:27.141 --> 36:28.316
To the Webber Method!Ah!

36:28.360 --> 36:30.188
[ Laughter ]

36:30.231 --> 36:31.885
[ Mugs clink ]

36:31.928 --> 36:35.193
♪♪

36:38.413 --> 36:44.289
♪♪

36:44.332 --> 36:47.335
I'm so sorry, Noah.
We did everything we could.

36:47.379 --> 36:51.339
Winston: Roy's lungs
were just...too far gone,

36:51.383 --> 36:53.820
and the damage put
too much stress on his heart.

36:56.431 --> 36:57.519
Owen: Noah...

36:57.563 --> 36:59.173
♪♪

36:59.217 --> 37:01.697
I can help you continue
Roy's work, you know,

37:01.741 --> 37:04.091
the data,
the testimonials.

37:04.134 --> 37:06.702
Yeah, I don't
want your help.

37:06.746 --> 37:10.228
I never wanted it in the first
place, but you convinced me.

37:10.271 --> 37:13.100
You convinced me to introduce
you to my friends,

37:13.143 --> 37:16.756
my family,
and look what happened.

37:16.799 --> 37:18.323
You made it
so much worse.

37:18.366 --> 37:25.417
♪♪

37:25.460 --> 37:32.293
♪♪

37:32.337 --> 37:36.079
You know, I almost left Jake
in the first lockdown,

37:36.123 --> 37:37.603
in the thick of it,
about two months in.

37:37.646 --> 37:39.300
I wasn't even drinking.
I was stone-cold sober.

37:39.344 --> 37:41.171
I just --
[ Chuckling ] God.

37:41.215 --> 37:43.261
They were bickering
about "Game of Thrones,"

37:43.304 --> 37:45.828
and I just
got up off the couch,

37:45.872 --> 37:48.614
got in the car,
and drove.

37:48.657 --> 37:50.093
Drove for about two hours

37:50.137 --> 37:52.095
before I stopped
and even thought to ask myself

37:52.139 --> 37:54.576
what I was doing.

37:54.620 --> 37:56.317
Are you asking
if I'm sure?

37:56.361 --> 37:57.797
I am saying that

37:57.840 --> 38:01.322
when one is in a slight
mental-health crisis,

38:01.366 --> 38:05.152
one might regret the decisions
she makes later.

38:05.195 --> 38:07.023
I didn't leave when I was
thinking about doing drugs.

38:07.067 --> 38:08.982
And I didn't leave
when I was wondering

38:09.025 --> 38:12.028
if Link would ever
really understand me.

38:12.072 --> 38:13.378
I stayed
through all of that

38:13.421 --> 38:14.944
because I thought
I must be crazy,

38:14.988 --> 38:16.729
because who leaves
a really good and decent guy?

38:16.772 --> 38:18.861
But I don't feel crazy now.

38:18.905 --> 38:20.602
And I don't
want to get high.

38:20.646 --> 38:22.169
I just don't want a ring,

38:22.212 --> 38:24.084
and I don't want to have
any more babies.

38:24.127 --> 38:26.652
And -- And I didn't
even leave him.

38:26.695 --> 38:29.176
He left me. But...

38:29.219 --> 38:30.830
[ Breathes deeply ]

38:30.873 --> 38:33.311
But I hated the life
that he loved,

38:33.354 --> 38:36.183
and so I think that
the sanest and kindest thing

38:36.226 --> 38:40.013
I could possibly do
is to let him go,

38:40.056 --> 38:43.146
no matter how much
it sometimes aches.

38:43.190 --> 38:44.626
[ Elevator bell dings,
doors open ]

38:44.670 --> 38:46.976
Look at you.

38:47.020 --> 38:49.414
♪♪

38:49.457 --> 38:51.329
Look at me, what?

38:51.372 --> 38:55.245
Look at you, Amelia Shepherd,
all grown up.

38:55.289 --> 38:58.553
♪♪

38:58.597 --> 39:01.339
♪ Pieces of my heart

39:01.382 --> 39:04.211
♪ Scatter like stones

39:04.254 --> 39:06.213
♪ And I'm just trying
to figure it out ♪

39:06.256 --> 39:08.607
Rough day?Yeah, I had better.

39:08.650 --> 39:10.130
Sorry to hear that.

39:10.173 --> 39:12.262
♪ For every one I find

39:12.306 --> 39:13.612
Hey, I don't want to talk
about it,

39:13.655 --> 39:15.918
but do you want to get
a drink at Joe's?

39:15.962 --> 39:17.964
I think I, um...

39:18.007 --> 39:19.269
I think I need a minute
before I go home

39:19.313 --> 39:20.967
to the wife and the kids.

39:21.010 --> 39:22.011
♪ I'm just trying
to puzzle peace ♪

39:22.055 --> 39:23.404
Yeah, sure.

39:23.448 --> 39:24.666
Sounds good.

39:24.710 --> 39:26.451
♪♪

39:26.494 --> 39:29.889
♪ I'm just trying
to get some sleep ♪

39:29.932 --> 39:31.891
♪♪

39:31.934 --> 39:34.937
♪ But the ocean of my heart
is raging ♪

39:34.981 --> 39:36.896
Hey.
Hey.

39:36.939 --> 39:38.376
What's up?

39:38.419 --> 39:39.594
[ Breathing heavily ]

39:39.638 --> 39:41.335
♪ I take a breath
and try to breathe ♪

39:41.379 --> 39:43.119
Mm!

39:43.163 --> 39:46.427
♪ I'm just trying
to puzzle peace ♪

39:46.471 --> 39:49.082
♪♪

39:49.125 --> 39:51.998
I-I heard you did two flawless
lap choles today.

39:52.041 --> 39:53.216
I did.

39:53.260 --> 39:55.131
My rock-star boyfriend.

39:55.175 --> 39:57.743
Huh?
Say it again.

39:57.786 --> 40:01.007
My rock-star boy--

40:01.050 --> 40:03.313
Meredith: I've had to operate
alone before...

40:03.357 --> 40:05.272
♪ Looking for answers

40:05.315 --> 40:07.796
...in circumstances I would
have never thought possible.

40:07.840 --> 40:10.712
♪ But wise words
only get me so far ♪

40:10.756 --> 40:11.887
We'll go home in a minute.

40:11.931 --> 40:13.889
♪ I'd pull it apart

40:13.933 --> 40:18.894
[ Yawning ] I just need to find
the energy to walk to the car

40:18.938 --> 40:20.679
and get in it...
[ Crunching ]

40:20.722 --> 40:23.072
...which might be tomorrow.

40:23.116 --> 40:25.292
By now, I know what
I'm capable of,

40:25.335 --> 40:27.512
how much I can handle
on my own.

40:27.555 --> 40:28.469
♪ I'm just trying
to get some sleep ♪

40:28.513 --> 40:30.210
And you know what?

40:30.253 --> 40:31.864
I can handle a lot.

40:31.907 --> 40:33.213
♪♪

40:33.256 --> 40:35.302
♪ But the ocean of my heart
is raging ♪

40:35.345 --> 40:36.825
You're playing
the surgery over and over

40:36.869 --> 40:38.566
in your head, right?

40:38.610 --> 40:39.828
[ Clicks tongue ]

40:39.872 --> 40:41.526
When you saw that
bloody field,

40:41.569 --> 40:46.748
you felt numb, but cold,

40:46.792 --> 40:49.098
and sick
to your stomach?

40:49.142 --> 40:51.318
Yeah. How'd you know?

40:51.361 --> 40:52.798
[ Chuckles ]

40:52.841 --> 40:55.496
You don't think I ever made
a mistake in the OR before?

40:55.540 --> 40:56.845
♪♪

40:56.889 --> 41:00.458
Or watched Meredith Grey
make a mistake?

41:00.501 --> 41:03.069
♪♪

41:03.112 --> 41:04.592
[ Sighs ]
I feel awful.

41:04.636 --> 41:06.420
You should.

41:06.464 --> 41:08.204
Thanks.

41:08.248 --> 41:12.382
If you didn't, you'd be
in the wrong line of work.

41:12.426 --> 41:17.126
It's that feeling, that --
that -- that awfulness --

41:17.170 --> 41:19.389
it sticks with us

41:19.433 --> 41:21.522
so we don't ever make
that same mistake again.

41:21.566 --> 41:23.524
♪♪

41:23.568 --> 41:25.308
It's how
we become great.

41:25.352 --> 41:27.833
♪ I'm just trying
to puzzle peace ♪

41:27.876 --> 41:29.269
[ Chuckles lightly,
breathes deeply ]

41:29.312 --> 41:31.184
Night, Helm.

41:31.227 --> 41:33.578
But that doesn't mean I'm
going to turn down an assist

41:33.621 --> 41:35.536
from another pair
of skilled hands.

41:35.580 --> 41:36.972
♪ Oh-oh

41:37.016 --> 41:38.234
♪ Oh-oh

41:38.278 --> 41:39.584
♪ Oh-oh

41:39.627 --> 41:40.846
♪ Oh-oh

41:40.889 --> 41:42.587
♪ Oh-oh

41:42.630 --> 41:44.502
♪ Oh-oh

41:44.545 --> 41:45.894
♪ Oh-oh

41:45.938 --> 41:47.548
Because at the end of the day,

41:47.592 --> 41:49.463
just because
I can do a surgery alone

41:49.507 --> 41:50.638
doesn't mean I have to.

41:50.682 --> 41:52.161
Hi.
Let me guess --

41:52.205 --> 41:53.598
emergent
kidney transplant.

41:53.641 --> 41:55.121
Uh, liver, actually.

41:55.164 --> 41:56.688
How'd it go?

41:56.731 --> 41:58.646
Good. No bad.
Good.

41:58.690 --> 42:00.082
You're here.

42:00.126 --> 42:02.084
I'm here.

42:02.128 --> 42:04.565
Should we
get some dinner tonight?

42:04.609 --> 42:05.784
Yes.
[ Chuckling ] Okay.

42:05.827 --> 42:06.959
Let's do it.Let's do it.

42:07.002 --> 42:08.134
Okay.
Okay.

42:08.177 --> 42:09.265
Go get some rest.
I will.

42:09.309 --> 42:10.440
See you.

42:10.484 --> 42:11.616
♪ I don't really know
what to say ♪

42:11.659 --> 42:13.269
Knowing someone else
has your back?

42:13.313 --> 42:15.620
♪ And I take a breath
and try to breathe ♪

42:15.663 --> 42:17.056
It's everything.

42:17.099 --> 42:18.361
♪♪

42:18.405 --> 42:21.800
♪ I'm just trying
to puzzle peace ♪

42:21.843 --> 42:23.062
♪♪

